            </span></a></div><div class="wsj-article-caption"><span class="wsj-article-credit">Jacob Stead</span> </div></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><h3> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tampa-why-gen-z-and-millennial-tourists-are-flocking-to-this-retirement-mecca-1e2be027?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Tampa: Why Gen Z and Millennial Tourists Are Flocking to This Retirement Mecca</a></h3><h4> Miami? Passé. Thanks to an influx of young travelers and residents drawn by its food and bar scene—and its walkability—this sleepy Sun Belt city is waking up fast. <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tampa-why-gen-z-and-millennial-tourists-are-flocking-to-this-retirement-mecca-1e2be027?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Read the story.</a> </h4><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-interactiveLink"><div class="image-container"> <a class="interactive-link" href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tampa-why-gen-z-and-millennial-tourists-are-flocking-to-this-retirement-mecca-1e2be027"><img width="16" height="10" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-814630?width=700&amp;height=560" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><span class="image-interactive-icon">
