"><div class="media-object-interactiveLink"><div class="image-container"> <a class="interactive-link" href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/into-the-bright-sunshine-review-hubert-humphreys-first-crusade-51f860b"><img width="16" height="10" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-816493?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><span class="image-interactive-icon">
            </span></a></div><div class="wsj-article-caption"><span class="wsj-article-credit">Wally Kammann/Star Tribune/Getty Images</span></div></div></div><p> The future presidential candidate&#39;s bold convention speech in 1948 pushed his party and the country toward ending racial segregation. <em>Review by Richard Aldous</em></p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/into-the-bright-sunshine-review-hubert-humphreys-first-crusade-51f860b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Read the review</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
